!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

patience /ˈpeɪʃəns/

1. N-UNCOUNT If you have patience , you are able to stay calm and not get annoyed, for example, when something takes a long time, or when someone is not doing what you want them to do. 耐心 

例： He doesn't have the patience to wait. 他没有耐心等。 

2. PHRASE If someone tries your patience or tests your patience , they annoy you so much that it is very difficult for you to stay calm. 考验某人的耐心极限 

例： He tended to stutter whenever he spoke to her, which tried her patience. 他一跟她讲话就结巴，这考验了她耐心极限。

</div>

